hopobject.body: Sorry, I'm busy at the moment welfil-20 aurochem Anna Samuil’s bleating Gutrune and Mikhail Petrenko’s woolly Hagen lowered the temperature a little with their appearances, but it never felt very long – even in the longest Wagnerian stretches – before such singers as Waltraud Meier (outstanding in Waltraute’s Narration) and Gerd Grochowski (Gunther) raised it again. With a little local help from the Royal Opera Chorus, strong as the testosterone-fuelled Vassals, this Berlin Ring has entered Proms lore.
